> we will run that pipeline on different environments, there will be
  different authentications to different systems, how would you set that
  we can have like a re-usable pipeline that we can use for multiple cases
  what would be kind of your thoughts in designing:

    - so basically, to design a reusable pipeline for multiple environments,
      my approach would be to make the pipeline parameterized and modular

    - to begin with, i would create a single piepline where environment details
      like Dev, QA or staging are passed as parameters

    - based on the selected environment, the pipeline can dynamically pick configurations
      like URL, credentials, and test data

    - for handling different automations, i would use jenkins credentials managements,
      where sensitive data like usernames, passwords, or tokens are stored securely and
      accessed during execution

    - from my experience, this avoids hardcoding and improves security,

    - next, i would maintain environment-specific configurations in separate files,
      like config files or property files, so that the pipeline logic remains
      the same while only configurations change

    - also, i would design the pipeline in modular way using reusable stages, so common
      steps like build, test, and report execution can be reused across environments

    - if needed, i would use shared libraries in jenkins to reuse common functions
      across multiple pipelines

    - so basically, by using parameterization, secure credentials handling and modular design,
      we can create a reusable pipeline that works across multiple environments efficiently
